# CPU Scheduler Simulator

A CPU scheduling simulator built as part of the Operating Systems course at Cairo University.

## Algorithms Implemented
- Round Robin (RR)
- Shortest Remaining Time First (SRTF)
- Highest Priority First (HPF)

## Features
- Terminal visualization of process state transitions
- Scheduling output showing waiting time and CPU utilization
- Buddy system memory management

## Tech Stack
C

## Notes
Team project at Cairo University. Note: some edge cases in algorithm consistency are still being worked on.
